{"name":"Bolt Gun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Boltguns, or bolters as they are often called, are the main weapon of the Space Marines, who carry versions so huge that few humans can easily lift one, let alone fire it. The lighter models others use to serve the Emperor are only slightly less destructive, but still powerful enough to destroy any who oppose His Will.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":7,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":24,"value":24},"reload":"Full","special":"Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/boltgun.png","effects":[],"_id":"06WmxlaPlBYU4Ym1"}
{"name":"Flintlock Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Exceptionally basic in both construction and operation, lintlocks are surprisingly common throughout the Imperium due the level of prestige attached to them. Finely-crafted lintlocks pass through Askellian generations as heirlooms, and some fetch enormous prices among high nobles and Rogue Traders alike. This pistol counts as a truncheon when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"common","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0XXN5HamCY4zfNDN"}
{"name":"Hellrifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Extremely effective weapons frowned upon by more Puritanical Inquisitors, hellrifles are intricate weapons that fire impossibly sharp shards of an unknown material. Speculated to be daemonic in origin, the true nature of this ammunition remains a mystery to the Adeptus Mechanicus, who have yet to recover even a single example for study.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":10,"class":"basic","type":"","range":300,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Felling (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0hdqjBaGQAA8m1TA"}
{"name":"Musket","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An improvement on the arquebus, the musket sufers fewer drawbacks with recoil and reload, making it an ideal weapon for ranks of feudal soldiers. A musket counts as a staf when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"common","weight":7,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"0vdh8hvxd7GT5knh"}
{"name":"Digi-Weapon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Impossibly advanced, the digi-weapons of the enigmatic Jokaero slip easily onto a user&rsquo;s fingers like rings and fire either with a simple press of a button or by squeezing the band. The weapons themselves vary immensely and never seem to completely run out of ammunition, a facet of their design that remains a mystery to the Adeptus Mechanicus.</p>\n<p>Table 2&ndash;1: Armoury Imperialis on page 44 lists the most common digi-weapon, which incorporates the profile of a laspistol. Other digi-weapon types can include ones incorporating the profile of a flamer, grav pistol, inferno pistol, needle pistol, plasma pistol, or others at the GM&rsquo;s discretion, by using that weapon&rsquo;s damage, penetration, and weapon qualities. The rate of fire, range, and clip size are always set to the values listed in Table 2&ndash;1: Armoury Imperialis (see page 44), no matter the weapon&rsquo;s normal values. Digi-weapons are worn as rings and do not prevent the hand from performing other tasks. They take one hour to recharge between shots, cannot be modified, and always have an Availability of Near Unique.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":0.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":3,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"34gZ5zujIWO9nWGw"}
{"name":"Lasgun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Lasguns are the basic weapon of Imperial Guard troopers, and as such are the most common las weapon in existence. They come in many varieties and patterns, and the continued survival of the Imperium owes much to their reliability, simplicity of design, and ease of use.</p>","availability":"common","weight":4,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/lasgun.png","effects":[],"_id":"3OzBgxgXFdVtbtHk"}
{"name":"Flamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A common weapon in many gangs and cults (who savour the smell of burning flesh), flamers relatively easy to construct and maintain. They do not rely on expert marksmanship, and are ideal for attacking enemies in cover or confined spaces with indiscriminate conflagrations.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Flame, Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/flamer.png","effects":[],"_id":"5dS4K14ss1HCjLqR"}
{"name":"Longflame","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Longlame is a primitive rocket launcher capable of sending a single warhead a signiicant distance, but without a great deal of accuracy. The heavy warhead explodes with considerable force, and leaves a lasting inferno to disrupt enemy movement. This rocket is a single use item and cannot be reloaded.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":6,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":200,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Blast (4), Flame, Inaccurate,  Primitive (8)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"6bRWeTxfdEWDRCqH"}
{"name":"Webber","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A webber weapon fires masses of jellied filaments, which expand in&nbsp;the air to form a web of sticky, near-unbreakable material. A favoured&nbsp;armament for Adeptus Arbites and&nbsp;bounty hunters alike, it can easily&nbsp;subdue violent mobs who would&nbsp;dare violate the Emperor&rsquo;s Law.&nbsp;Once entangled, few can escape&nbsp;from the constricting threads.&nbsp;The filaments becomes brittle and&nbsp;dissolve away after 1d5 hours.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":50,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Full","special":"Blast (5), Snare (1)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9P9FxG9l5wAUwJxv"}
{"name":"Gorgon Chemical Flamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Favoured by the followers of more fanatical Ordo Hereticus Inquisitors, the Gorgon utilises corrosive chemicals that leave any survivors with debilitating injuries and lingering sickness. Its specialised design prevents the use of other types of Flame weapon ammunition.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Corrosive,  Felling (1), Flame, Spray, Toxic (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"AR3h7CiSLIk4MSgQ"}
{"name":"Laspistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Compact and reliable, laspistols are a favourite weapon for Imperial officers and gang leaders alike.</p>","availability":"common","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":30,"value":30},"reload":"Half","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/wh40k/laspistol.png","effects":[],"_id":"Cl0xsRpv7YakEmTd"}
{"name":"Cerberus Heavy Flamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Magnus-Pattern Heavy Flamer&mdash;known for its triple-barrelled design&mdash;appears in many Askellian militaries as well as witch hunting warbands. Its weight includes the backpack fuel supply.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":40,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":8,"value":8},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Flame, Reliable, Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GOTZsPmOP6KPKKS8"}
{"name":"Laslock","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>On worlds where the standard power pack pattern has been lost, laslocks are commonly used in place of lasguns. Often found in the hands of desperate and poorly equipped insurgents or renegades, laslocks might be scratch-built or modifications of antique or damaged las rifles brought back into service by scav-workshops and heretek forges. A laslock&rsquo;s jury-rigged cells are temperamental things at best, but still potent, firing a more powerful discharge than that of a standard lasgun. Laslocks do not benefit from the Las Weapon Variable Setting rules.</p>","availability":"plentiful","weight":4,"class":"basic","type":"","range":70,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/laslock.png","effects":[],"_id":"JyG7WTwOcM9Ge1Rf"}
{"name":"Graviton Gun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These exceedingly rare relics from the Dark Age of Technology&nbsp;are sacred devices jealously guarded by the Adeptus Mechanicus,&nbsp;who very rarely allow one outside of their armouries. Each fires&nbsp;arcane particles that disrupt the gravimetric fields surrounding the&nbsp;target, using the victim&rsquo;s own armoured mass against him. The&nbsp;terrible, crushing force of the unnatural energies reduces targets&nbsp;to ruptured hulls and crumpled armoured forms. Most common&nbsp;are graviton guns, though grav pistols and grav combi-weapons&nbsp;can also be found in elite warbands and Mechanicum tech-heresy&nbsp;capture units.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"impact","penetration":"8","clip":{"max":9,"value":9},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Concussive (2), Graviton","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KNO6wqlAw3piTyaY"}
{"name":"Arquebus","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A weapon that exempliies the brute force approach of most black powder weapons, the arquebus is the most common firearm found on Askellian feudal worlds. It can knock a man in full plate of his feet with a single shot, but the recoil, smoke, and reload time make the weapon impractical in the heat of melee fighting. If a character with a Strength bonus of 3 or less uses this weapon, it counts as a Heavy weapon instead of Basic weapon. When fired, an arquebus also creates a cloud with the Smoke (1) quality centred on the firer that lasts for 1d5-1 rounds.</p>","availability":"common","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":45,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"impact","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Concussive (1),  Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LsW9L7KQYSUlRCH9"}
{"name":"Missile Launcher","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Missile launchers fire heavy shells with great explosive power, and are well-suited to puncturing enemy armour or decimating assaulting cultists. The portable version is lighter than the regular military model, and is normally used shoulder-mounted or strongly braced against a wall or siding. Many users have someone nearby to aid in carrying the large shells and reloading between shots.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":35,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":300,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"NFeTFcsvy2jscE2T"}
{"name":"Heavy Flamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Large and terrifying, heavy flamers use two muzzles to create huge blasts of fire that can incinerate entire swaths of enemies in a single shot. Only the strongest can carry the weapon as well as the massive backpack of fuel it requires, but its presence has turned the tide against many a heretical attack.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":45,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":10,"value":10},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Flame, Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/heavyflamer.png","effects":[],"_id":"SKYfzUD88SqJPWJx"}
{"name":"Web Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A webber weapon fires masses of jellied filaments, which expand in the air to form a web of sticky, near-unbreakable material. A favoured armament for Adeptus Arbites and bounty hunters alike, it can easily subdue violent mobs who would dare violate the Emperor&rsquo;s Law. Once entangled, few can escape from the constricting threads. The filaments becomes brittle and dissolve away after 1d5 hours.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":3.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Full","special":"Snare (0)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VSIzbaHWMwZcMtn2"}
{"name":"Purgatus Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A mix of a crossbow and a shotgun, the Purgatus is an ancient pattern unique to the Ordo Hereticus. Designed to launch handcrafted wooden stakes inlaid with puriied silver runes that disrupt psykers and Daemons alike, the Purgatus is a precision weapon and symbol of Inquisitorial supremacy. The Purgatus can use any type of shotgun and crossbow ammunition, as well as its own Purgatus Stakes (see page 47).</p>","availability":"rare","weight":16,"class":"basic","type":"","range":50,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":5,"value":5},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XMDOVwoI26Ep1DV4"}
{"name":"Holo-Spectus","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Consisting of a powerful launching tube, a long-range pictrecorder, and a holographic display, the holo-spectus allows its user to survey a large area to plan movements, seek out targets, or even find his bearings. Aimed skyward, the compact launcher blasts the fist-sized recorder several hundred metres vertically into the air, where it floats on tiny grav plating, feeding what it sees to a three-dimensional holographic display on the base-unit. As the user turns on the spot, so does the floating recorder, allowing the user to see kilometres in every direction. With a simple flick of a switch, the recorder zeroes in on the base unit and returns to the launcher in a matter of seconds. Successfully firing a holo-spectus into the air requires a Challenging (+0) Tech-Use test, after which the user gains a visual representation of the area below the hovering pict-recorder out for several kilometres. The control interface allows the Acolyte to zoom and highlight parts of the holographic display, and turning on the spot causes the recorder above to turn, allowing the Acolyte to survey the area around him in great detail, which grants a +20 bonus to Navigate (Surface), Survival (Tracking), and Scrutiny tests. The recorder can stay airborne for 5 hours before its power cell is exhausted.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":600,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XfTmvSzpzkD5PwMu"}
{"name":"Bow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Though bows come in a multitude of shapes and are made from a wide variety of materials, their basic form and function has changed little throughout the millennia. Even where the Mechanicum may be ascendant, a well-placed and silent arrow can be just as effective as a revered boltgun. A bow always requires both hands to use.</p>","availability":"common","weight":2,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Primitiv (6), Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YkVwUrKtmmXHPKdg"}
{"name":"Firesprite Needler","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A design common to assassins and those who wish to remain discreet, and thus popular on Snope&rsquo;s World, the firesprite uses an integral forearm mounting. Possessing a prodigious rate of fire, the weapon often drains its ammunition reserves&mdash;kept in a magazine under the forearm&mdash;within a few seconds. The firesprite needler has the Compact, Forearm Weapon Mounting, and Silencer modifications (see pages 162&ndash;164 of the Dark Heresy Core Rulebook).</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":4,"full":8},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"rending","penetration":"","clip":{"max":16,"value":16},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Toxic (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aMIiJb50TFW5kHYd"}
{"name":"Quillgun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Originally created to fire toxins tailored for specific Askellian xenos threats, the quillgun would be a rare and highly soughtafter weapon for Inquisitors and Rogue Traders alike if not for a clerical error that saw Selvanus Binary manufacture this weapon in enormous numbers. The esteemed dart gun now floods the Faceless Trade, where outlaws and smugglers use readily available chemicals to capture valuable specimens for sale, slavery, and other unscrupulous ends. When Acquired, the quillgun comes with one clip each of Ataractic and Venenum rounds, the only types of ammunition it can use. The weapon has the Silencer modification.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":120,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":3,"value":3},"reload":"Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cLZkdNltrZZA5vkz"}
{"name":"Hot-shot Laspistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Specialised variants of the&nbsp;standard las weapon design, hotshot&nbsp;weapons use stronger power&nbsp;packs that provide extra energy for each shot.&nbsp;High ranking military officers and elite forces&nbsp;such as the Militarum Tempestus use them frequently, but other&nbsp;Imperial agencies with sufficient means also favour the extra&nbsp;stopping power they provide against heretics and other threats.&nbsp;Hot-shot weapons use a 10 kg backpack power source rather&nbsp;than a standard plug-in pack, even for the smaller hot-shot pistol.&nbsp;Larger packs mean greater power behind each shot, but make&nbsp;reloading more impractical, which is a trade-off most are willing&nbsp;to make. Hot-shot weapons can also be linked to larger backpacks&nbsp;for additional ammunition (see page 162). Hot-shot weapons do&nbsp;not benefit from the Las Weapon Variable Setting rules.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":4,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"7","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/hot-shot_laspistol.png","effects":[],"_id":"dRpvwYnSgX7cPYdD"}
{"name":"Drake’s Claw","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This primitive rocket ires a thin-shelled warhead, and is named for the Rogue Trader who scofed at its outlandish appearance. The direct damage is minimal, but as Drake discovered, the payload breaks into viciously lethal splinters that are horriic to remove. This rocket is a single use item and cannot be reloaded.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":6,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":200,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Blast (3), Crippling (1), Inaccurate, Primitive (7), Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dpKnNoBUhZqLVLiu"}
{"name":"Psycannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"good","description":"<p>Seen only in the hands of influential Daemonhunters, psycannons fire explosive shells tipped with Truesilver. Capable of smashing through psychic defences, each shell contains a small latticework of psycho-conductive fibres that allow the user to channel some of his own psychic power into each bolt. Psycannons have integral suspensor technology, granting the wielder the Auto-Stabilised trait while in use, and are always of at least Good craftsmanship. They ignore all protective benefits granted by psychic powers and inflict +2 additional damage for every point of the wielder&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":20,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":120,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":2,"full":5},"damage":"2d10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"3 Full","special":"Daemonbane, Reliable, Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dvlotuY4uNFb6JOt"}
{"name":"Hand Flamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Also known as flame pistols or burners, these small weapons are ideal for close-range fighting, where their very short range and poor accuracy are less important than their furious effect.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":3.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":10,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":2,"value":2},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Flame, Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/handflamer.png","effects":[],"_id":"e4rAcWZRM2pUXQEe"}
{"name":"Godwyn-De’az Storm Bolter","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The expertly crafted Godwyn-De&rsquo;az line of bolters are more than just weapons of war. They are handcrafted artefacts&mdash;their components sanctiied and blessed at every step of construction&mdash; and icons of devotion. Untold billions of heretics have fallen before the howl of these holy weapons, and they remain fearful symbols of the Adepta Sororitas across the Imperium. Such weapons are normally only available to Acolytes with the Adepta Sororitas background&mdash;those without it must provide a rationale to their GM when attempting to acquire these items.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":8,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":80,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":4},"damage":"1D10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"Full","special":"Reliable, Storm, Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"inZEptIvQBvP68gL"}
{"name":"Needle Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Needle weapons use a thin laser beam to fire crystalline slivers coated with virulent toxins, each shot as silent as it is lethal. They excel against unarmoured foes, but almost any protection can successfully blunt needle rounds. Those wounded often fall dead before they know they have been hit. Needle pistols make excellent backup weapons for infiltrating spies and thieves, while snipers prize the larger needle rifles which offer much greater range. Needle weapons count as having a built-in silencer (see page 164).</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"Full","special":"Accurate, Felling (1), Toxic (5)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ioXUMtYmFw3bE3lY"}
{"name":"Heavy Bolter","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This huge weapon is rarely used outside of military forces, but sometimes is all that stands against some of the terrors of the Ruinous Powers. The larger shells carry additional propellant and stronger explosive charges, making them deadly against armoured foes at long ranges.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":40,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":150,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":6},"damage":"1d10+8","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"Full","special":"Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons/heavybolter.png","effects":[],"_id":"keSoGQcE3FZGvrVE"}
