{"name":"Snapper Repeating Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Found only on a few Askellian worlds, the Snapper Repeating Rile represents the pinnacle of black powder engineering. Functionally similar to a musket, the Snapper features a rotating cylinder that holds eight individual shots to lessen the need for reloading. If a Snapper&rsquo;s wielder uses it as an improvised melee weapon and scores two or more degrees of failure on the Weapon Skill test, its mechanisms snap and it is damaged.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":45,"class":"basic","type":"","range":50,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":8,"value":8},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Overheats, Primitive (8), Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"n555mpxfOm4Wqelo"}
{"name":"Condemnor","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Extremely hard to acquire within the Askellon Sector, the Condemnor Boltgun is a highly-specialised combi-weapon found almost exclusively in the hands of Ordo Hereticus Inquisitors and their Acolytes. It combines a boltgun with a single-shot crossbow armature that can be loaded with a variety of bolts, and between the two deadly ammunitions, surely no heretic can survive.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Accurate, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oDzbD5ApnDxPI5vR"}
