{"name":"Bolas","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>An ancient weapon often seen with hive city bounty hunters and feral worlders alike, bolas have swirling weights at the ends of ropes or wires to entangle a target and often knock him to the ground. Once wrapped up, the foe is easily dispatched or further bound for transport and delivery.</p>","availability":"average","weight":0,"class":"thrown","type":"","range":10,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"","special":"Inaccurate, Snare (1)","attack":1.5},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"rKTiVfFLt1GBIeBu"}
{"name":"Incinerator","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Usually gifted to Ordo Malleus Inquisitors of rare skill, incinerators use psychically impregnated promethium that burns mortal flesh and unholy skin with equal ferocity. An Incinerator ignores any protective benefits granted by psychic powers, and targets in its area of effect suffer a &ndash;10 penalty on Agility tests to avoid the flames for each point of the wielder&rsquo;s psy rating.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":3,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":10,"value":10},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Daemonbane, Flame, Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"sg199TlZ2c4bMAOj"}
{"name":"Bolt Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Both a status symbol and puissant weapon, bolt pistols are rare in numbers but always feared. In the hands of an Imperial Guard Commissar, one can reverse a cowardly retreat; in the hands of an Inquisitor, it can stop a cult leader from summoning an unholy Daemon. Such is their power, both symbolic and physical, that many eagerly sacrifice all to possess one.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":3.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":8,"value":8},"reload":"Full","special":"Tearing","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"modules/DH2e_Resources/icons//boltpistol.png","effects":[],"_id":"t0H0WeW2uY6Avh67"}
{"name":"Grav Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These exceedingly rare relics from the Dark Age of Technology are sacred devices jealously guarded by the Adeptus Mechanicus, who very rarely allow one outside of their armouries. Each fires arcane particles that disrupt the gravimetric fields surrounding the target, using the victim&rsquo;s own armoured mass against him. The terrible, crushing force of the unnatural energies reduces targets to ruptured hulls and crumpled armoured forms. Most common are graviton guns, though grav pistols and grav combi-weapons can also be found in elite warbands and Mechanicum tech-heresy capture units.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"Full","special":"Concussive (1), Graviton","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tEs8pTlY4I3QEMFv"}
{"name":"Castigator Heavy Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Something of an oddity for a forge world with a reputation for advanced technology, this ostentatious device ires bolts almost a full metre in length and can put a man on the ground with even a glancing hit. Whenever a Castigator inlicts damage (after reductions for Armour and Toughness bonus) on a target that has the Size trait with a value of 5 or lower, that target is knocked Prone.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":12,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":70,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"impact","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":14,"value":14},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Concussive (2),  Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tJLTR5j2mzdhaiGf"}
{"name":"Hydra Flamer Array","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Magnus-Pattern Flamer Array is not a single weapon, but in fact several lamers strapped to each forearm with tubes leading to a high-pressure fuel canister. Usually worn under heavy robes, the Hydra allows its user to wave his arms back and forth spewing an unrelenting torrent of ire. The efect is nothing short of terrifying, and the Hydra has a prized reputation for breaking up crowds of cultists, seditionists, and other would-be heretics. When a character ires a Hydra Flamer Array, he gains the Fear (1) trait until the end of the encounter. The Hydra&rsquo;s Spray quality afects a 90&deg; cone, rather than the usual 30&deg; arc for weapons with this quality Its weight includes the backpack fuel supply.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":10,"class":"basic","type":"","range":8,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":10,"value":10},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Flame,  Proven (3), Spray","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vRMCGyJnGaMm4RWI"}
{"name":"Integration Cannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Another of Core Theta&rsquo;s eccentric designs, the cannon uses the principals of graviton weaponry, but with a wildly different effect. It projects a pulsing orb of gravitic energy that shatters on contact. A second later, the rapid mass increase draws anything nearby towards the centre, crushing it in a gruesome manner. After being fired, the cannon creates a gravitic anomaly within the area of its Blast quality that persists for 1d5 rounds. Whenever a character begins his turn in this area, he must make a Hard (&ndash;20) Dodge (Strength) test. If he fails, he is Immobilized until the end of his turn and suffers a single automatic hit to a randomly determined location for 4d10+4 Impact damage with penetration 8.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":65,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"4d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"8","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"3 Full","special":"Blast (5), Concussive (0), Inaccurate","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vXTeqxLrlAuHFN2K"}
{"name":"Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Crossbows are more compact than regular bows, but require additional mechanical fittings and usually have a shorter range.</p>","availability":"common","weight":3,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Primitiv (7)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ve6Yr932eMgr5j45"}
{"name":"Silverseine Launcher","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A specialist class of weapon designed to subdue and capture Daemons, silverseine launchers fire sheets of wiring laced with Truesilver. The nets rarely needs to hold Daemons for long, though, as the sanctified metals painfully eat away at their flesh and helps banish them back to the Warp. Silverseine launchers double their Snare value against characters with the Daemonic trait. Any such adversary trapped in a silverseine net must also test for Warp Instability at the start of each round.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":25,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Blast (4), Reliable, Sanctified, Snare (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wwXj8yLFuvxWbIXd"}
{"name":"Grenade Launcher","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This weapon uses compressed gas charges to fire grenades either directly or in indirect blasts against unseen foes, and is a common suppressive weapon in many battles. The grenade launcher uses grenades as its ammo (see page 157). When the character reloads the grenade launcher, he can choose any six grenades of the same type to load into the grenade launcher. For the next attacks before reloading again, the damage, penetration, and special sections of the grenade launcher&rsquo;s profile use the stats from the profile for the chosen type of grenade.</p>","availability":"average","weight":12,"class":"basic","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ygwv5umvlEw6XpIS"}
{"name":"Deliverance Light Crossbow","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Manufactured in small quantities across a number of Askellian feudal worlds, the Deliverance is a peculiar weapon that sacriices the punch of regular crossbows for a faster reload time. Usable in one hand or even as a wrist-mount, the Deliverance is a quiet and easily-concealed weapon. If given a forearm weapon mounting, the Deliverance&rsquo;s range is not reduced. Tests to ind a concealed Deliverance sufer a &ndash;20 penalty, and it counts as having a built-in silencer (see page 164 of the DARK HERESY Core Rulebook).&nbsp;</p>","availability":"rare","weight":1,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10","damageType":"rending","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"half","special":"Primitive (7)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zJDK4JHdlDJ7UwPy"}
{"name":"Inferno Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These pistols are nearly impossible to manufacture any more, and almost all that exist are ancient relics of ages long ago. Possessing an inferno pistol is a sign of status, and few but the powerful and influential have the honour of owning one of these valuable devices.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":10,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"12","clip":{"max":3,"value":3},"reload":"Full","special":"Melta","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vf8fZM5voiCCiqG3"}
{"name":"Meltagun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Meltaguns are a favourite weapon for anti-tank specialists, who use their close-range destructive power to cut through armourplate and heavy bulkheads alike.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":15,"class":"basic","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"12","clip":{"max":5,"value":5},"reload":"Full","special":"Melta","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"QIqQBzF2JTNyC5Cg"}
{"name":"Plasma Gun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Many plasma guns date back centuries or even millennia, and it is common for an ally to recover one rather than rescue its fallen user if there is no time for both. Despite the hazards a plasma gun can pose, those who carry one know it is a special honour few others can comprehend.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":18,"class":"basic","type":"","range":90,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+7","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"5 Full","special":"Maximal, Overheats","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZrhhLx44cVEAfNOX"}
{"name":"Plasma Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Each of these small weapons contains the fury of a burning star. A hit can rip apart even heavily armoured enemies in a single incandescent blast, as if the Emperor had turned His gaze upon the foes.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":4,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"energy","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":10,"value":10},"reload":"3 Full","special":"Maximal, Overheats","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1JlGhRpmos9OCH2a"}
{"name":"Sentinel Plasma Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A Cerix Magnus design perfected by the dogmatic scrutiny of Selvanus Binary, the Sentinel pulse rile eliminates the usual drawbacks of plasma weaponry by changing the nature of the energy discharge, through smaller pulses rather than large bolts. This pattern also includes a higher rate of ire and a better targeting system. Designed in tandem with the Praetor Armour of the Ebon Guard, Askellian collectors go to great lengths to acquire one.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":20,"class":"basic","type":"","range":120,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":5,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":40,"value":40},"reload":"Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3mHWPnJiMIL1XQ0Y"}
{"name":"Autocannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Autocannons are heavy, powerful weapons that can devastate light vehicles and armoured foes alike with long ranged firepower. They are commonly mounted on tanks or crewed with infantry teams in Imperial armies, but can also be found in the unclean hands of insurrectionists and heretical forces.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":40,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":300,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"3d10+8","damageType":"impact","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":24,"value":24},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"8G4ZtdpAaFfjMJdq"}
{"name":"Autogun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>While not as commonplace as lasguns in military formations, many local forces rely on these sturdy and inexpensive weapons to defend their home world from threats within or without. They use common, low-calibre shells in standardised clips, and can be set to fire in single, semi-automatic, or full-automatic modes making them as versatile as they are simple to construct and supply.</p>","availability":"average","weight":5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":30,"value":30},"reload":"Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fTuTVNq9W2lEm8Ht"}
{"name":"Autopistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Rapid firing and compact, many veteran Guardsmen carry an autopistol to supplement their regulation lasgun or other, less reliable weapons. They are also popular in gang hierarchies, and have settled many underhive leadership disputes in a hail of shells.</p>","availability":"average","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":6},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":18,"value":18},"reload":"Ful","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wD5qS9Py6v0okQas"}
{"name":"Hand Cannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This stub gun variant concentrates on stopping power above all else. It is a huge and brutal weapon, and those who use it generally do not care about the state of their target after the shot. Hand cannons kick like a grox and, unless used with two hands or a Recoil Glove, impose a &ndash;10 penalty on Ballistic Skill tests.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":35,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":5,"value":5},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cVyE0S9N8bGJTViF"}
{"name":"Heavy Stubber","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Heavy stubbers are common both on the battlefield and in the underhive, as many times there is little difference between the two locations. Relatively simple to produce and maintain, they use standard ammunition that can provide a hail of suppressive fire against infantry and light vehicles. Few have the muscles to fire one, especially with its infamous recoil, so most users rely on a bipod or other support. Like all stub weapons, heavy stubbers come in many forms and use many ammunition intakes, such as long belt feeds, huge clips, or wide drums.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":30,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":8},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":80,"value":80},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"vQ9xT2G6uEbdjh6Q"}
{"name":"Shotgun","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Shotguns are relatively easy to produce, and their wide area of effect makes them appealing for those unskilled in ranged combat. Their short range and low shot velocity can be detrimental in larger conflicts, but these qualities make them the perfect weapons for shipboard combat. The standardised shell construction also allows them to take a wide variety of specialised ammunition.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":8,"value":8},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Scatter","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cUZdJVnv8xiME3hx"}
{"name":"Shotgun (Combat)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Shotguns are relatively easy to produce, and their wide area of effect makes them appealing for those unskilled in ranged combat. Their short range and low shot velocity can be detrimental in larger conflicts, but these qualities make them the perfect weapons for shipboard combat. The standardised shell construction also allows them to take a wide variety of specialised ammunition.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":6.5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":18,"value":18},"reload":"Full","special":"Scatter","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cEQhJIvfLAre2tG9"}
{"name":"Sniper Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Less advanced than the elite needle rifles, sniper rifles are still very effective against most lightly armoured foes. When the gun is combined with a tripod brace and telescopic sight, a skilled marksman can easily turn the tides of a battle with a single shot.</p>","availability":"scarce","weight":5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":200,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":20,"value":20},"reload":"Full","special":"Accurate, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"gVSqQ9G6d7LqT6q2"}
{"name":"Stub Automatic","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Unlike the stub revolver, this pistol weapon can fire in rapid semiautomatic mode as well as single shots. Like the autopistol, it is easy to produce and maintain, but less accurate at longer ranges.</p>","availability":"average","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":9,"value":9},"reload":"Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"dVEOwGpaAes2wJj5"}
{"name":"Stub Revolver","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Revolvers use a rotary feed for fire single shots, with a small clip that must be manually replenished. Their open design makes it easy to load in custom rounds for special situations, and thus many bounty hunters and trackers find them useful backup weapons.</p>","availability":"plentiful","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+3","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"KVSFW8L7VJD1OCv9"}
{"name":"Shardcarbine","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>A more compact version of the basic splinter rifle, this weapon is often used in boarding actions to capture fresh slaves, and also features prominently in some of the xenos mercenary bands that operate in Askellian space. Though it has a shorter range, the shard carbine makes up for this with greater firepower.&nbsp;</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":3,"class":"basic","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":5},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":150,"value":150},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Storm, Toxic (1)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"C4sZ793Wy3nejYWh"}
{"name":"Shuriken Cannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 107.901px; top: 609.638px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.831938);\">his weapon grants the firer the Auto-Stabilised trait when in use.</span></p>\n<p>The most powerful portable shuriken weapon, these cannons can rip apart light armour. They are very useful in decimating entire groups, as each burst unleashes a horrific volley of firepower.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":18,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"rending","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":200,"value":200},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Razor Sharp, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"GkFdHmVPQoI2skJo"}
{"name":"Shuriken Catapult","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The standard armament for the citizen-soldiers of Eldar craftworlds, like all shuriken weapons they use gravitic accelerators to fire slices of plasti-crystal at tremendous velocities. The hail of razored discs can slice apart limbs before a target knows it is under attack.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":2.5,"class":"basic","type":"","range":80,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":120,"value":120},"reload":"Full","special":"Razor Sharp, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"YaNeSY4S3rkQg17a"}
{"name":"Shuriken Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Relatively common for Eldar weaponry, many in the Faceless Trade carry one of these pistols to both impress and intimidate. Members of the Cerulean Pact especially admire shuriken pistols as a sign of their prowess in smuggling Eldar devices.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1.2,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"Full","special":"Razor Sharp, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"jZQecxzjdjyFFoRs"}
{"name":"Splinter Cannon","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 107.901px; top: 609.638px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.831938);\">This weapon grants the firer the Auto-Stabilised trait when in use.</span></p>\n<p>Large yet still relatively lightweight, splinter cannons can puncture personal armour to ensure their payload of venomous ammunition tortures flesh, to the delight of their users.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":5,"class":"heavy","type":"","range":110,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"rending","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":300,"value":300},"reload":"3 Full","special":"Tearing, Toxic (4)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XZwqLPKFo8uBbvKY"}
{"name":"Splinter Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Often found with both sadistic Eldar slavers and those hunting them, these pistols are the smallest type of splinter weapon, but are still as cruel and deadly as any other. Firing slivers of poisoned crystals, they ensure painful deaths. Many splinter pistols have bladed attachments, and as such each counts as a knife with the Mono weapon modification when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":1.5,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":120,"value":120},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Toxic (1)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"cxj3ewBMWPXTVLZj"}
{"name":"Splinter Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These rifles are the mainstay weapon for the dark xenos in slave raids and piratical raids. Often the only signs of assaults from such users are the remnants of the bloodsoaked splinter-crystals littering now-empty settlements or colonies. Many splinter rifles have cruel bladed or spiked metal attachments, and as such each counts as a spear with the Mono weapon modification when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":2,"class":"basic","type":"","range":80,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":5},"damage":"1d10+2","damageType":"rending","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":180,"value":180},"reload":"","special":"Toxic (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JEaDPNQlYqXHEXlF"}
{"name":"Big Shoota","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 101.499px; top: 952.221px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.84546);\">When used by an Ork, this weapon loses the Unreliable special quality.</span></p>\n<p>The largest shoota used by most Orks, big shootas spray crude bullets and shell casings in all directions, much to the delight of their owners. So long as they are loud and impressive, few greenskins care if they actually hit their targets.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":120,"rateOfFire":{"single":0,"burst":0,"full":10},"damage":"1d10+6","damageType":"impact","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":60,"value":60},"reload":"2 Full","special":"Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SHU7tGa57MU0w6ie"}
{"name":"Burna (Ranged)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 101.499px; top: 952.221px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.84546);\">When used by an Ork, this weapon loses the Unreliable special quality.</span></p>\n<p>A terrifying weapon of surprising sophistication&mdash;at least by Ork standards&mdash;it combines a highly volatile flamer with a dangerous short-ranged cutting torch. Useful for everything from herding squigs to carving holes in hull plating, burnas fulfil a variety of roles within Ork society. The burna has two profiles (one for melee and one for ranged combat), and requires two hands to use in either mode. Its weight includes the backpack fuel tank.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"energy","penetration":"2","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"Full","special":"Flame, Spray, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3YaLRN1EXRJoRXor"}
{"name":"Rokkit Launcha","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 101.499px; top: 952.221px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.84546);\">When used by an Ork, this weapon loses the Unreliable special quality.</span></p>\n<p>Little more than an oversized warhead stuck to a basic launching mechanism, these crude ballistic weapons embody an Ork&rsquo;s innate need to make things blow up. Wildly inaccurate and packed with enough explosives to wreck heavy vehicles, most Orks find the simple act of firing one an exhilarating experience and actually hitting the target an almost secondary consideration.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":150,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"6","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Blast (2), Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZTEo6oXN5gFlFi5v"}
{"name":"Shoota","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 101.499px; top: 952.221px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.84546);\">When used by an Ork, this weapon loses the Unreliable special quality.</span></p>\n<p>Aside from the more specialised equipment such as burnas and rokkit launchas, the majority of Ork ranged weaponry encompasses a collection of solid projectile weapons referred to as shootas. Superficially similar to autoguns, shootas hurl heavy hand-made slugs capable of punching a fist-sized hole into a target. Luckily, Orks are anything but accurate, and they mostly enjoy the noise these weapons make when fired.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":4,"class":"basic","type":"","range":50,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":30,"value":30},"reload":"Full","special":"Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"WThiZ5jL5s3jdlRn"}
{"name":"Slugga","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p><span dir=\"ltr\" style=\"left: 101.499px; top: 952.221px; font-size: 13.48px; font-family: serif; transform: scaleX(0.84546);\">When used by an Ork, this weapon loses the Unreliable special quality.</span></p>\n<p>Though relatively small, these pistols are as filled with dakka as any other Ork weapon. Gang leaders and Faceless Traders sometimes carry them as signs of their brutal combat skills, for few weapons impress criminals and heretics alike as much as greenskin weapons do.</p>","availability":"rare","weight":2,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":20,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+4","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":18,"value":18},"reload":"Full","special":"Inaccurate, Unreliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"C7IFTG7l1n2JZjBK"}
{"name":"Kroot Rifle (Pulse Round)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This rifle, perhaps the signature weapon of the entire race, does little more but add to the mystery of just how advanced the Kroot really are as a species. In stark contrast to other weaponry the Kroot use, it seems almost primitive&mdash;a simple device festooned with totems and fetishes that also doubles as a bladed staff. The rifle&rsquo;s ammunition is anything but, however, and fires bolts of plasma (or in some cases, high-density sniper rounds) over long distances. Easily the most common Kroot weapon in the Askellon Sector, a Kroot rifle still fetches a good price for traders. A Kroot rifle counts as a staff with the Mono weapon upgrade when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":110,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+5","damageType":"energy","penetration":"1","clip":{"max":6,"value":6},"reload":"2 Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"4zPS7jY6AoHMUR3S"}
{"name":"Kroot Rifle (Sniper Round)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This rifle, perhaps the signature weapon of the entire race, does little more but add to the mystery of just how advanced the Kroot really are as a species. In stark contrast to other weaponry the Kroot use, it seems almost primitive&mdash;a simple device festooned with totems and fetishes that also doubles as a bladed staff. The rifle&rsquo;s ammunition is anything but, however, and fires bolts of plasma (or in some cases, high-density sniper rounds) over long distances. Easily the most common Kroot weapon in the Askellon Sector, a Kroot rifle still fetches a good price for traders. A Kroot rifle counts as a staff with the Mono weapon upgrade when used in melee combat.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":110,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+7","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Accurate","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"3mLEuK5cefrVTXH4"}
{"name":"Pulse Carbine","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Few examples of a pulse weapon exists outside of Kroot hands in Askellian space, making the weapon&rsquo;s details yet another aspect of their enigma. Each pulse carbine contains an integrated grenade launcher, making it capable of firing photon grenades as well as the standard plasma pulse rounds.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":3},"damage":"2d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":24,"value":24},"reload":"Full","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"FSndY0dHBjpX2FIX"}
{"name":"Pulse Carbine (Photon Grenade)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Few examples of a pulse weapon exists outside of Kroot hands in Askellian space, making the weapon&rsquo;s details yet another aspect of their enigma. Each pulse carbine contains an integrated grenade launcher, making it capable of firing photon grenades as well as the standard plasma pulse rounds.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":0.5,"class":"launched","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Blast (12)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HKcXpNW2fb1BeGMh"}
{"name":"Pulse Pistol","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>These pistols, like all pulse weapons, feature gyroscopic stabilisation to aid in marksmanship. Few Kroot use them, however, favouring the brutality of their own knives and bladed rifles instead, to the puzzlement of the Askellian Magi Xenologis.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":40,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+2","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":16,"value":16},"reload":"Half","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"irnoxZ1oSv1A4Fws"}
{"name":"Pulse Rifle","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The Askellian Machine Cult regard pulse weapons with disdain for their heretical designs, yet many seek them out to discover the methods the weapons use to contain and fire their distinctive plasma pulses. The rifle version is seen both in the hands of xenos hunters and in the guarded displays of hive nobles eager to impress fellow collectors of alien artefacts.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":8,"class":"basic","type":"","range":150,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":4},"damage":"2d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":36,"value":36},"reload":"Half","special":"","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"Dy7UuFbdbZgpSjsG"}
{"name":"Ablative Projector","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The most common weapon found within cache D-216-98, the ablative projector emits a glowing emerald beam that reduces flesh, armour, and anything else it touches to atoms within seconds.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":10,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":2,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+8","damageType":"energy","penetration":"5","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Reliable, Vengeful (9)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"bQUzHIU0QOFlqj1i"}
{"name":"Cascade Lance (Ranged)","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Originally thought to be an ornate staff for melee combat, an accidental (and devastating) activation revealed it also fires a tightly focused beam of exotic particles with enough power to melt tank hulls and reduce living creatures to ash. A cascade lance requires two hands to wield when it is used as a melee weapon.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":6,"class":"basic","type":"","range":15,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"1d10+12","damageType":"energy","penetration":"10","clip":{"max":1,"value":1},"reload":"Half","special":"Proven (5), Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"I4mcOc07ZCCXUbHJ"}
{"name":"Concussion Beamer","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>This compact weapon appears to utilise a form of anti-matter that none of the Askellian Tech-Priests can fathom. The near-invisible blast of energy explodes violently on contact, and can tear targets in half with a single burst.</p>","availability":"near-unique","weight":4,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":30,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+5","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"4","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Concussive (1), Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"eOyrQYpRkoT2XZ1J"}
{"name":"Resonance Arc","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Instead of an expected exotic particle beam, when the adepts of Core Theta first managed to activate this device, it instead emitted a single arc of lightning that danced across the laboratory. Tech-Priests and servitors alike were killed before the arc dissipated, leaving behind shattered bionics and scorched skeletons. When a character using a resonance arc rolls a 9 or 10 for damage, or kills a target, a bolt of electricity arcs from the original target to a randomly selected target within 5 metres, inflicting an additional automatic hit with the weapon&rsquo;s profile on the new target&rsquo;s Body location. This extra hit can result in further additional hits as the arc leaps from target to target.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":20,"class":"basic","type":"","range":75,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10+3","damageType":"energy","penetration":"3","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Shocking, Reliable","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"9YuUPN9mf7aTE19O"}
{"name":"Guldaniri Bile Projector","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Although little evidence of their civilisation remains, the weapons of the Guldaniri continue to terrorise Low Worlds across Rubicon. Their bile projectors fire bursts of a concentrated caustic liquid powerful enough to melt flesh and armour alike. Popular with the Faceless Trade, these weapons are dangerously easy to find, something many Ordo Xenos Inquisitors find troubling.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":11,"class":"basic","type":"","range":60,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"3d10","damageType":"energy","penetration":"","clip":{"max":10,"value":10},"reload":"3 Full","special":"Blast (2), Corrosive, Toxic (2)","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"EfmS0nSkWQdXdTIW"}
{"name":"Neural Catalyser","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>Seemingly made from pure crystal, the neural catalyser has no moving parts, trigger, power source, or any clear indications of how it functions. Fired by squeezing the grip, the catalyser sends a stream of energy that tears not at the body, but the mind. Samples have been discovered across the sector, leading many to wonder at the extent of whatever (hopefully) dead race created the weapons.</p>\n<p>Damage inflicted by a neural catalyser ignores armour, and is reduced by the target&rsquo;s Willpower bonus instead of its Toughness bonus. Whenever a hit from a neural catalyser inflicts damage on a target (after reduction for Willpower bonus), the target also suffers 1d5 Willpower damage.</p>","availability":"extremely-rare","weight":3,"class":"pistol","type":"","range":35,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":0,"full":0},"damage":"2d10","damageType":"explosive","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":0,"value":0},"reload":"","special":"Concussive (3), Overheats","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"aHafN1hIMT6TZa8x"}
{"name":"Xenarch Death-Arc","permission":{"default":0,"Q8i5xjnghNCdqNHG":3},"type":"weapon","data":{"craftsmanship":"common","description":"<p>The death-arc of the distant and possibly extinct Xenarch species unleashes a crackling bolt of energy that, once it hits, forms a conduit between the gun and its victim. The longer the exposure, the more electrical energy the gun channels into the target. When a character wielding a Xenarch death-arc would inflict multiple hits from a single attack using this weapon, he instead resolves a single hit against the first hit location he struck as part of the attack. This hit inflicts 1d10+3 additional Energy damage for each hit he would have inflicted beyond the first.</p>","availability":"very-rare","weight":10,"class":"basic","type":"","range":100,"rateOfFire":{"single":1,"burst":3,"full":6},"damage":"","damageType":"impact","penetration":"0","clip":{"max":90,"value":90},"reload":"Full","special":"Inaccurate, Shocking","attack":0},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VVbZSltCQM2xAtel"}
